---
import DocLayout from "../../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/Global.css";
---

<DocLayout title="Quick Start">
    <section id="quick-start">
        <h1 class="docs-title">Quick Start (Usage Guide)</h1>

        <div class="docs-intro-section" id="achieve">
            <h2 class="docs-subtitle">What You’ll Achieve</h2>
            <p class="docs-paragraph">
                If you just installed AstroAnimate and want to make it work
                immediately, this quick start solves that exact task.
            </p>
            <p class="docs-paragraph">By the end of this page, you will:</p>
            <ul class="docs-list">
                <li>Build a working Astro page with AstroAnimate components</li>
                <li>Understand the recommended import pattern</li>
                <li>Use both CSS-first and opt-in enhancement patterns</li>
                <li>Verify behavior in development quickly</li>
                <li>Know what to do next for API-level adoption</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="docs-paragraph">
                This page focuses on practical implementation, not theory.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="docs-intro-section" id="prerequisites">
            <h2 class="docs-subtitle">Prerequisites / Requirements</h2>
            <p class="docs-paragraph">
                Before starting this AstroAnimate quick start:
            </p>
            <p class="docs-paragraph">
                AstroAnimate is installed in your project:
            </p>
            <div class="docs-code-block">
                <div class="code-header">
                    <span>bash</span>
                </div>
                <div class="code-wrapper">
                    <pre><code><span class="keyword">npm</span> install <span class="string">@astroanimate/core</span></code></pre>
                    <button class="copy-btn-icon" aria-label="Copy code">
                        <svg
                            width="24"
                            height="24"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            fill="none"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            stroke-linecap="round"
                            stroke-linejoin="round"
                            ><rect
                                x="9"
                                y="9"
                                width="13"
                                height="13"
                                rx="2"
                                ry="2"></rect><path
                                d="M5 15H4a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V4a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h9a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v1"
                            ></path></svg
                        >
                    </button>
                </div>
            </div>
            <ul class="docs-list">
                <li>
                    Your Astro version is compatible ('<span class="keyword"
                        >^4.0.0 || ^5.0.0</span
                    >')
                </li>
                <li>You can run your project locally with npm scripts</li>
                <li>
                    You have a page ready to edit, such as '<span
                        class="component">src/pages/index.astro</span
                    >'
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p class="docs-paragraph">
                If installation is not done yet, complete '<span
                    class="component">/docs/installation/</span
                >' first.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="docs-intro-section" id="step-by-step">
            <h2 class="docs-subtitle">Step-by-Step Guide</h2>

            <div class="steps-container">
                <!-- STEP 1 -->
                <div class="step-item" id="qs-step-1">
                    <h3 class="step-title">
                        Step 1: Create a minimal working page
                    </h3>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">
                        Open src/pages/index.astro and add:
                    </p>
                    <div class="docs-code-block">
                        <pre><code><span class="comment">---</span>
<span class="component">import</span> &#123; FadeIn, SlideIn, TextRotate &#125; <span class="component">from</span> <span class="string">"@astroanimate/core"</span>;
<span class="component">import</span> <span>SlideIn</span> <span class="component">from</span> <span class="string">"@astroanimate/core/SlideIn"</span>;
<span class="component">import</span> <span>TextRotate</span> <span class="component">from</span> <span class="string">"@astroanimate/core/TextRotate"</span>;
<span class="comment">---</span>

&lt;<span class="brand">main</span>&gt;
  &lt;<span class="brand">div</span> <span class="string">class</span>=<span class="component">"container"</span>&gt;
    &lt;<span class="brand">FadeIn</span> <span class="string">advance</span> <span class="string">direction</span>=<span class="component">"up"</span> <span class="string">distance</span>={<span class="number">{20}</span>} <span class="string">once</span>&gt;
      &lt;<span class="brand">h1</span>&gt;
        AstroAnimate is installed
      &lt;/<span class="brand">h1</span>&gt;
    &lt;/<span class="brand">FadeIn</span>&gt;

    &lt;<span class="brand">SlideIn</span> <span class="string">enter</span> <span class="string">direction</span>=<span class="component">"left"</span> <span class="string">delay</span>={<span class="number">{0.2}</span>} <span class="string">threshold</span>={<span class="number">{0.5}</span>}&gt;
      &lt;<span class="brand">p</span>&gt;Welcome to the usage guide.&lt;/<span class="brand">p</span>&gt;
    &lt;/<span class="brand">SlideIn</span>&gt;

    &lt;<span class="brand">TextRotate</span> <span class="string">items</span>={<span class="number">["Fast", "Modern", "Dynamic"]</span>} /&gt;
  &lt;/<span class="brand">div</span>&gt;
&lt;/<span class="brand">main</span>&gt;</code></pre>
                    </div>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">Why this code:</p>
                    <ul class="docs-list">
                        <li>It validates real component imports.</li>
                        <li>
                            It demonstrates three common usage patterns:
                            <ul
                                class="docs-list"
                                style="margin-top: 12px; margin-bottom: 0;"
                            >
                                <li>rotating text</li>
                                <li>fade-in entry</li>
                                <li>reveal-on-scroll</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>It matches the project’s example style.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <!-- STEP 2 -->
                <div class="step-item" id="qs-step-2">
                    <h3 class="step-title">
                        Step 2: Understand the component responsiveness
                    </h3>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">
                        Use a direct component import for a clear first
                        validation:
                    </p>
                    <div class="docs-code-block">
                        <pre><code><span class="comment">---</span>
<span class="component">import</span> <span>FadeIn</span> <span class="component">from</span> <span class="string">"@astroanimate/core/FadeIn"</span>;
<span class="comment">---</span>

&lt;<span class="brand">main</span>&gt;
  &lt;<span class="brand">FadeIn</span> <span class="string">advance</span> <span class="string">direction</span>=<span class="component">"up"</span> <span class="string">distance</span>={<span class="number">{20}</span>} <span class="string">once</span>&gt;
    &lt;<span class="brand">h1</span>&gt;AstroAnimate is installed&lt;/<span class="brand">h1</span>&gt;
  &lt;/<span class="brand">FadeIn</span>&gt;
&lt;/<span class="brand">main</span>&gt;</code></pre>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- STEP 3 -->
                <div class="step-item" id="qs-step-3">
                    <h3 class="step-title">
                        Step 3: Optional: import from root exports
                    </h3>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">
                        AstroAnimate components generally follow:
                    </p>
                    <ol class="docs-numbered-list">
                        <li>
                            Render baseline content first
                            <span class="docs-paragraph"
                                >(visible HTML/CSS output)
                            </span>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Enable optional enhancement
                            <span class="docs-paragraph"
                                >when needed with props like '<span
                                    class="string">enhance</span
                                >'
                            </span>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Tune behavior with component props
                            <span class="docs-paragraph"
                                >('<span class="string">direction</span>', ' <span
                                    class="string">distance</span
                                >', '<span class="string">delay</span>', etc.)
                            </span>
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">
                        This gives a practical balance between performance and
                        interaction.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <!-- STEP 4 -->
                <div class="step-item" id="qs-step-4">
                    <h3 class="step-title">Step 4: Run and verify</h3>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">Start dev server:</p>
                    <div class="docs-code-block dark-bg">
                        <!-- <div class="code-header">
                            <span>bash</span>
                        </div> -->
                        <div class="code-wrapper">
                            <pre><code>npm run dev</code></pre>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <p class="docs-paragraph">Then verify:</p>
                    <ul class="docs-list">
                        <li>Page renders without import/module errors</li>
                        <li>
                            `<span class="string">TextRotate</span>` cycles
                            through the `<span class="string">texts</span
                            >` array
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            `<span class="string">FadeIn</span>` and `<span
                                class="string">Reveal</span
                            >` animate when enhancement conditions are met
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Content remains usable if enhancements are disabled
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="docs-intro-section" id="notes">
            <h2 class="docs-subtitle">Notes</h2>
            <div class="steps-list">
                <div class="step-item">
                    <ul class="docs-list">
                        <li>
                            Use the exact package namespace: @astroanimate/core.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Prefer explicit component imports for clarity when
                            onboarding teams.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Some interactions are enhancement-based; test in
                            real browser conditions.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Respect reduced-motion preferences during QA for
                            accessibility behavior.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            For advanced timeline choreography, consider whether
                            additional motion tooling is needed.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="docs-intro-section" id="related-resources">
            <h2 class="docs-subtitle">Related Resources</h2>
            <ul class="docs-list docs-resource-links">
                <li>→ <a href="/docs">Introduction</a></li>
                <li>→ <a href="/docs/installation">Installation</a></li>
                <li>→ <a href="/docs/components">Supported Components</a></li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="docs-intro-section" id="faq">
            <h2 class="docs-subtitle">FAQ (Developer Questions)</h2>
            <div class="faq-container">
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary
                        >Is AstroAnimate only for Astro? <svg
                            class="chevron"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            fill="none"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            ><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg
                        ></summary
                    >
                    <div class="faq-content">Yes. It is fully built for.</div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary
                        >How do I use AstroAnimate in a real Astro page quickly? <svg
                            class="chevron"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            fill="none"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            ><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg
                        ></summary
                    >
                    <div class="faq-content">
                        Install @astroanimate/core, import 1–3 components
                        into src/pages/index.astro, and validate behavior
                        with npm run dev.
                    </div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary
                        >Should I create a separate usage page if I already have
                        quick start? <svg
                            class="chevron"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            fill="none"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            ><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg
                        ></summary
                    >
                    <div class="faq-content">
                        Yes. Use Quick Start for first successful
                        implementation. Use Component API pages for
                        component-by-component patterns, props, and advanced
                        examples.
                    </div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary
                        >Is enhance required for all AstroAnimate components? <svg
                            class="chevron"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            fill="none"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            ><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg
                        ></summary
                    >
                    <div class="faq-content">
                        No. Usage depends on component behavior. Some components
                        are CSS-first by default, while others expose optional
                        enhancement for interactive scenarios.
                    </div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary
                        >What is the best first component to try? <svg
                            class="chevron"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            fill="none"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            ><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg
                        ></summary
                    >
                    <div class="faq-content">
                        Use FadeIn for first validation because it is easy to
                        inspect visually and simple to configure.
                    </div>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                    <summary
                        >How do I know my setup is production-safe?<svg
                            class="chevron"
                            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                            fill="none"
                            stroke="currentColor"
                            stroke-width="2"
                            ><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg
                        ></summary
                    >
                    <div class="faq-content">
                        Run build, typecheck, lint, and test scripts before
                        rollout. Then verify behavior in your target browsers
                        and devices.
                    </div>
                </details>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="docs-footer-nav">
            <a href="/docs/installation" class="prev-link">
                <span class="label">PREVIOUS</span>
                <span class="title">
                    <svg
                        width="18"
                        height="18"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        fill="none"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                        stroke-width="2"
                        stroke-linecap="round"
                        stroke-linejoin="round"
                        style="transform: rotate(180deg);"
                        ><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"></line><polyline
                            points="12 5 19 12 12 19"></polyline></svg
                    >
                    Installation
                </span>
            </a>
            <a href="/docs/supported-platforms" class="next-link">
                <span class="label">NEXT</span>
                <span class="title">
                    Supported Platforms
                    <svg
                        width="18"
                        height="18"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        fill="none"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                        stroke-width="2"
                        stroke-linecap="round"
                        stroke-linejoin="round"
                        ><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"></line><polyline
                            points="12 5 19 12 12 19"></polyline></svg
                    >
                </span>
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <Fragment slot="toc">
        <div class="toc-header">IN THIS PAGE</div>
        <nav class="toc-nav">
            <a href="#achieve" class="active">What You'll Achieve</a>
            <a href="#prerequisites">Prerequisites</a>
            <a href="#step-by-step">Step-by-Step Guide</a>
            <a href="#qs-step-1" class="toc-sub">Step 1: Minimal working page</a
            >
            <a href="#qs-step-2" class="toc-sub"
                >Step 2: Understand responsiveness</a
            >
            <a href="#qs-step-3" class="toc-sub">Step 3: Root exports</a>
            <a href="#qs-step-4" class="toc-sub">Step 4: Run and verify</a>
            <a href="#notes">Notes</a>
            <a href="#faq">FAQ</a>
            <a href="#related-resources">Related Resources</a>
        </nav>
    </Fragment>
</DocLayout>
